{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":947,"text":"The story starts:\nI was at a friend's house,"},{"time":4342,"text":"and she had on her shelf\na copy of the DSM manual,"},{"time":8404,"text":"which is the manual of mental disorders."},{"time":10640,"text":"It lists every known mental disorder."},{"time":13934,"text":"And it used to be, back in the '50s,\na very slim pamphlet."},{"time":16991,"text":"And then it got bigger\nand bigger and bigger,"},{"time":19640,"text":"and now it's 886 pages long."},{"time":22746,"text":"And it lists currently\n374 mental disorders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27448,"text":"So I was leafing through it,"},{"time":28856,"text":"wondering if I had any mental disorders,"},{"time":31797,"text":"and it turns out I've got 12."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33482,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":34657,"text":"I've got generalized anxiety disorder,"},{"time":37379,"text":"which is a given."},{"time":38649,"text":"I've got nightmare disorder,"},{"time":40689,"text":"which is categorized"},{"time":42078,"text":"if you have recurrent dreams of being\npursued or declared a failure,"},{"time":46142,"text":"and all my dreams involve people\nchasing me down the street"},{"time":49841,"text":"going, \"You're a failure!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":51489,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":53296,"text":"I've got parent-child relational problems,"},{"time":56422,"text":"which I blame my parents for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58391,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":60310,"text":"I'm kidding. I'm not kidding."},{"time":62692,"text":"I'm kidding."},{"time":64628,"text":"And I've got malingering."},{"time":65888,"text":"And I think it's actually quite rare"},{"time":67648,"text":"to have both malingering\nand generalized anxiety disorder,"},{"time":70688,"text":"because malingering tends\nto make me feel very anxious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73423,"text":"Anyway, I was looking through this book,"},{"time":75435,"text":"wondering if I was much crazier\nthan I thought I was,"},{"time":78060,"text":"or maybe it's not a good idea to diagnose\nyourself with a mental disorder"},{"time":81617,"text":"if you're not a trained professional,"},{"time":83767,"text":"or maybe the psychiatry profession\nhas a kind of strange desire"},{"time":88664,"text":"to label what's essentially normal\nhuman behavior as a mental disorder."},{"time":93054,"text":"I didn't know which of these was true,\nbut I thought it was kind of interesting,"},{"time":96856,"text":"and I thought maybe I should\nmeet a critic of psychiatry"},{"time":99740,"text":"to get their view,"},{"time":101148,"text":"which is how I ended up having\nlunch with the Scientologists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104510,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":105770,"text":"It was a man called Brian,\nwho runs a crack team of Scientologists"},{"time":110292,"text":"who are determined to destroy\npsychiatry wherever it lies."},{"time":114584,"text":"They're called the CCHR."},{"time":116597,"text":"And I said to him, \"Can you prove to me"},{"time":119572,"text":"that psychiatry is a pseudo-science\nthat can't be trusted?\""},{"time":123652,"text":"And he said, \"Yes,\nwe can prove it to you.\""},{"time":125863,"text":"And I said, \"How?\""},{"time":127300,"text":"And he said, \"We're going\nto introduce you to Tony.\""},{"time":131093,"text":"And I said, \"Who's Tony?\""},{"time":132974,"text":"And he said, \"Tony's in Broadmoor.\""},{"time":136307,"text":"Now, Broadmoor is Broadmoor Hospital."},{"time":138641,"text":"It used to be known as the Broadmoor\nAsylum for the Criminally Insane."},{"time":143299,"text":"It's where they send the serial killers,"},{"time":145759,"text":"and the people who can't help themselves."},{"time":147839,"text":"And I said to Brian,\n\"Well, what did Tony do?\""},{"time":151020,"text":"And he said, \"Hardly anything."},{"time":154168,"text":"He beat someone up or something,"},{"time":157130,"text":"and he decided to fake madness\nto get out of a prison sentence."},{"time":162249,"text":"But he faked it too well,\nand now he's stuck in Broadmoor"},{"time":166786,"text":"and nobody will believe he's sane."},{"time":169271,"text":"Do you want us to try and get you\ninto Broadmoor to meet Tony?\""},{"time":173032,"text":"So I said, \"Yes, please.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":175386,"text":"So I got the train to Broadmoor."},{"time":176934,"text":"I began to yawn uncontrollably\naround Kempton Park,"},{"time":181053,"text":"which apparently is what dogs\nalso do when anxious,"},{"time":183459,"text":"they yawn uncontrollably."},{"time":185736,"text":"And we got to Broadmoor."},{"time":187458,"text":"And I got taken through gate\nafter gate after gate after gate"},{"time":191935,"text":"into the wellness center, which is where\nyou get to meet the patients."},{"time":195456,"text":"It looks like a giant Hampton Inn."},{"time":198918,"text":"It's all peach and pine\nand calming colors."},{"time":202853,"text":"And the only bold colors\nare the reds of the panic buttons."},{"time":209067,"text":"And the patients started drifting in."},{"time":212148,"text":"And they were quite overweight\nand wearing sweatpants,"},{"time":215753,"text":"and quite docile-looking."},{"time":217436,"text":"And Brian the Scientologist\nwhispered to me,"},{"time":220199,"text":"\"They're medicated,\""},{"time":222133,"text":"which, to the Scientologists,\nis like the worst evil in the world,"},{"time":225376,"text":"but I'm thinking\nit's probably a good idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227981,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":230096,"text":"And then Brian said, \"Here's Tony.\""},{"time":233159,"text":"And a man was walking in."},{"time":235165,"text":"And he wasn't overweight,\nhe was in very good physical shape."},{"time":238293,"text":"And he wasn't wearing sweatpants,"},{"time":240620,"text":"he was wearing a pinstripe suit."},{"time":243034,"text":"And he had his arm outstretched"},{"time":245054,"text":"like someone out of The Apprentice."},{"time":247138,"text":"He looked like a man\nwho wanted to wear an outfit"},{"time":250444,"text":"that would convince me\nthat he was very sane."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255003,"text":"And he sat down."},{"time":256178,"text":"And I said, \"So is it true\nthat you faked your way in here?\""},{"time":259503,"text":"And he said, \"Yep. Yep. Absolutely.\nI beat someone up when I was 17."},{"time":262971,"text":"And I was in prison awaiting trial,"},{"time":265077,"text":"and my cellmate said to me,"},{"time":266416,"text":"'You know what you have to do?"},{"time":267924,"text":"Fake madness."},{"time":269912,"text":"Tell them you're mad, you'll get\nsent to some cushy hospital."},{"time":273547,"text":"Nurses will bring you pizzas,\nyou'll have your own PlayStation.'\""},{"time":277402,"text":"I said, \"Well, how did you do it?\""},{"time":279118,"text":"He said, \"Well, I asked to see\nthe prison psychiatrist."},{"time":281885,"text":"And I'd just seen a film called 'Crash,'"},{"time":284196,"text":"in which people get sexual pleasure\nfrom crashing cars into walls."},{"time":288323,"text":"So I said to the psychiatrist,"},{"time":290296,"text":"'I get sexual pleasure\nfrom crashing cars into walls.'\""},{"time":294085,"text":"And I said, \"What else?\""},{"time":295534,"text":"He said, \"Oh, yeah.\nI told the psychiatrist"},{"time":298211,"text":"that I wanted to watch women as they died,"},{"time":301519,"text":"because it would make\nme feel more normal.\""},{"time":303708,"text":"I said, \"Where'd you get that from?\""},{"time":305454,"text":"He said, \"Oh, from a biography\nof Ted Bundy that they had"},{"time":308262,"text":"at the prison library.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":310489,"text":"Anyway, he faked madness\ntoo well, he said."},{"time":313740,"text":"And they didn't send him\nto some cushy hospital."},{"time":316234,"text":"They sent him to Broadmoor."},{"time":318539,"text":"And the minute he got there,"},{"time":319900,"text":"said he took one look at the place,\nasked to see the psychiatrist,"},{"time":323030,"text":"said, \"There's been\na terrible misunderstanding."},{"time":325572,"text":"I'm not mentally ill.\""},{"time":327772,"text":"I said, \"How long have you been here for?\""},{"time":330062,"text":"He said, \"Well, if I'd just\ndone my time in prison"},{"time":332432,"text":"for the original crime,\nI'd have got five years."},{"time":335572,"text":"I've been in Broadmoor for 12 years.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":340911,"text":"Tony said that it's a lot harder\nto convince people you're sane"},{"time":344964,"text":"than it is to convince them you're crazy."},{"time":347472,"text":"He said, \"I thought\nthe best way to seem normal"},{"time":349719,"text":"would be to talk to people\nnormally about normal things"},{"time":352363,"text":"like football or what's on TV."},{"time":354265,"text":"I subscribe to New Scientist,"},{"time":356027,"text":"and recently they had an article"},{"time":357718,"text":"about how the U.S. Army was training\nbumblebees to sniff out explosives."},{"time":362102,"text":"So I said to a nurse,"},{"time":363545,"text":"'Did you know that the U.S. Army\nis training bumblebees"},{"time":366168,"text":"to sniff out explosives?'"},{"time":368587,"text":"When I read my medical notes,\nI saw they'd written:"},{"time":371386,"text":"'Believes bees can sniff out explosives.'\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":374422,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":376000,"text":"He said, \"You know, they're always\nlooking out for nonverbal clues"},{"time":379131,"text":"to my mental state."},{"time":380895,"text":"But how do you sit in a sane way?"},{"time":383556,"text":"How do you cross your legs in a sane way?"},{"time":385852,"text":"It's just impossible.\""},{"time":387676,"text":"When Tony said that to me,"},{"time":388957,"text":"I thought to myself,\n\"Am I sitting like a journalist?"},{"time":392847,"text":"Am I crossing my legs like a journalist?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":396072,"text":"He said, \"You know, I've got\nthe Stockwell Strangler on one side of me,"},{"time":401168,"text":"and I've got the 'Tiptoe\nThrough the Tulips' rapist"},{"time":403581,"text":"on the other side of me."},{"time":404972,"text":"So I tend to stay in my room a lot\nbecause I find them quite frightening."},{"time":408445,"text":"And they take that as a sign of madness."},{"time":410730,"text":"They say it proves\nthat I'm aloof and grandiose.\""},{"time":414693,"text":"So, only in Broadmoor would not wanting\nto hang out with serial killers"},{"time":418513,"text":"be a sign of madness."},{"time":420124,"text":"Anyway, he seemed completely normal\nto me, but what did I know?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":423914,"text":"And when I got home I emailed\nhis clinician, Anthony Maden."},{"time":426758,"text":"I said, \"What's the story?\""},{"time":428356,"text":"And he said, \"Yep.\nWe accept that Tony faked madness"},{"time":431891,"text":"to get out of a prison sentence,\nbecause his hallucinations --"},{"time":435681,"text":"that had seemed\nquite cliche to begin with --"},{"time":437856,"text":"just vanished the minute\nhe got to Broadmoor."},{"time":440498,"text":"However, we have assessed him,"},{"time":442727,"text":"and we've determined that what he is"},{"time":445164,"text":"is a psychopath.\""},{"time":446983,"text":"And in fact, faking madness"},{"time":448815,"text":"is exactly the kind of cunning\nand manipulative act of a psychopath."},{"time":453205,"text":"It's on the checklist:\ncunning, manipulative."},{"time":456150,"text":"So, faking your brain going wrong"},{"time":457751,"text":"is evidence that your brain\nhas gone wrong."},{"time":461007,"text":"And I spoke to other experts,"},{"time":462603,"text":"and they said the pinstripe\nsuit -- classic psychopath --"},{"time":466566,"text":"speaks to items one\nand two on the checklist:"},{"time":468868,"text":"glibness, superficial charm\nand grandiose sense of self-worth."},{"time":472709,"text":"And I said, \"Well, but why didn't\nhe hang out with the other patients?\""},{"time":476345,"text":"Classic psychopath -- it speaks\nto grandiosity and also lack of empathy."},{"time":480718,"text":"So all the things that had seemed\nmost normal about Tony"},{"time":484206,"text":"was evidence, according to his clinician,"},{"time":487255,"text":"that he was mad in this new way."},{"time":489430,"text":"He was a psychopath."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490857,"text":"And his clinician said to me, \"If you\nwant to know more about psychopaths,"},{"time":494406,"text":"you can go on a psychopath-spotting course"},{"time":497635,"text":"run by Robert Hare, who invented\nthe psychopath checklist.\""},{"time":500546,"text":"So I did."},{"time":501730,"text":"I went on a psychopath-spotting course,"},{"time":503797,"text":"and I am now a certified --"},{"time":507998,"text":"and I have to say, extremely adept --\npsychopath spotter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512934,"text":"So, here's the statistics:"},{"time":516203,"text":"One in a hundred regular people\nis a psychopath."},{"time":520995,"text":"So there's 1,500 people in his room."},{"time":524852,"text":"Fifteen of you are psychopaths."},{"time":529831,"text":"Although that figure rises to four percent\nof CEOs and business leaders,"},{"time":534837,"text":"so I think there's a very good chance"},{"time":537596,"text":"there's about 30 or 40\npsychopaths in this room."},{"time":542734,"text":"It could be carnage\nby the end of the night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545192,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":549672,"text":"Hare said the reason why\nis because capitalism at its most ruthless"},{"time":554592,"text":"rewards psychopathic behavior --"},{"time":557260,"text":"the lack of empathy, the glibness,"},{"time":562221,"text":"cunning, manipulative."},{"time":564603,"text":"In fact, capitalism, perhaps\nat its most remorseless,"},{"time":567592,"text":"is a physical manifestation\nof psychopathy."},{"time":572117,"text":"It's like a form of psychopathy\nthat's come down to affect us all."},{"time":577307,"text":"Hare said, \"You know what?\nForget about some guy at Broadmoor"},{"time":580202,"text":"who may or may not have faked madness."},{"time":582041,"text":"Who cares? That's not a big story."},{"time":583686,"text":"The big story,\" he said,\n\"is corporate psychopathy."},{"time":586603,"text":"You want to go and interview yourself\nsome corporate psychopaths.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":590956,"text":"So I gave it a try.\nI wrote to the Enron people."},{"time":594163,"text":"I said, \"Could I come\nand interview you in prison,"},{"time":596533,"text":"to find out it you're psychopaths?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":598327,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":599581,"text":"And they didn't reply."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600881,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":602455,"text":"So I changed tack."},{"time":604376,"text":"I emailed \"Chainsaw Al\" Dunlap,"},{"time":607676,"text":"the asset stripper from the 1990s."},{"time":611239,"text":"He would come into failing businesses"},{"time":613470,"text":"and close down 30 percent\nof the workforce,"},{"time":615529,"text":"just turn American towns into ghost towns."},{"time":618697,"text":"And I emailed him and I said,"},{"time":620174,"text":"\"I believe you may have\na very special brain anomaly"},{"time":622992,"text":"that makes you ... special,"},{"time":625027,"text":"and interested in the predatory\nspirit, and fearless."},{"time":629412,"text":"Can I come and interview you\nabout your special brain anomaly?\""},{"time":632888,"text":"And he said, \"Come on over!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":634730,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":636115,"text":"So I went to Al Dunlap's\ngrand Florida mansion."},{"time":639191,"text":"It was filled with sculptures\nof predatory animals."},{"time":644262,"text":"There were lions and tigers --\nhe was taking me through the garden --"},{"time":647925,"text":"there were falcons and eagles,"},{"time":650641,"text":"he was saying, \"Over there\nyou've got sharks and --\""},{"time":653169,"text":"he was saying this\nin a less effeminate way --"},{"time":655406,"text":"\"You've got more sharks\nand you've got tigers.\""},{"time":661106,"text":"It was like Narnia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662830,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":666332,"text":"And then we went into his kitchen."},{"time":668772,"text":"Now, Al Dunlap would be brought in\nto save failing companies,"},{"time":672948,"text":"he'd close down 30 percent\nof the workforce."},{"time":675395,"text":"And he'd quite often\nfire people with a joke."},{"time":678598,"text":"Like, for instance,\none famous story about him,"},{"time":680967,"text":"somebody came up to him and said,\n\"I've just bought myself a new car.\""},{"time":684443,"text":"And he said, \"Well,\nyou may have a new car,"},{"time":686475,"text":"but I'll tell you what you\ndon't have -- a job.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":691542,"text":"So in his kitchen --"},{"time":692722,"text":"he was in there with his wife, Judy,\nand his bodyguard, Sean --"},{"time":695704,"text":"and I said, \"You know\nhow I said in my email"},{"time":697784,"text":"that you might have a special brain\nanomaly that makes you special?\""},{"time":701444,"text":"He said, \"Yeah, it's an amazing\ntheory, it's like Star Trek."},{"time":704370,"text":"You're going where\nno man has gone before.\""},{"time":706606,"text":"And I said, \"Well --\" (Clears throat)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":709734,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":711087,"text":"Some psychologists might say"},{"time":714274,"text":"that this makes you --\"\n(Mumbles)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":716976,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":718627,"text":"And he said, \"What?\""},{"time":720841,"text":"And I said, \"A psychopath.\""},{"time":722169,"text":"And I said, \"I've got a list\nof psychopathic traits in my pocket."},{"time":726572,"text":"Can I go through them with you?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":729393,"text":"And he looked intrigued despite himself,"},{"time":731510,"text":"and he said, \"Okay, go on.\""},{"time":732909,"text":"And I said, \"Okay.\nGrandiose sense of self-worth.\""},{"time":736316,"text":"Which I have to say, would\nhave been hard for him to deny,"},{"time":739116,"text":"because he was standing\nunder a giant oil painting of himself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742524,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":746699,"text":"He said, \"Well, you've\ngot to believe in you!\""},{"time":749756,"text":"And I said, \"Manipulative.\""},{"time":752668,"text":"He said, \"That's leadership.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":754385,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":755410,"text":"And I said, \"Shallow affect,"},{"time":757840,"text":"an inability to experience\na range of emotions.\""},{"time":760136,"text":"He said, \"Who wants to be weighed\ndown by some nonsense emotions?\""},{"time":763766,"text":"So he was going down\nthe psychopath checklist,"},{"time":765961,"text":"basically turning it\ninto \"Who Moved My Cheese?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":769186,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":772302,"text":"But I did notice something happening\nto me the day I was with Al Dunlap."},{"time":775746,"text":"Whenever he said anything to me\nthat was kind of normal --"},{"time":778667,"text":"like he said \"no\" to juvenile delinquency,"},{"time":781634,"text":"he said he got accepted into West Point,"},{"time":783564,"text":"and they don't let\ndelinquents in West Point."},{"time":786443,"text":"He said \"no\" to many short-term\nmarital relationships."},{"time":789183,"text":"He's only ever been married twice."},{"time":790867,"text":"Admittedly, his first wife\ncited in her divorce papers"},{"time":793838,"text":"that he once threatened her with a knife"},{"time":796302,"text":"and said he always wondered\nwhat human flesh tasted like,"},{"time":799043,"text":"but people say stupid things to each other"},{"time":801109,"text":"in bad marriages\nin the heat of an argument,"},{"time":803188,"text":"and his second marriage\nhas lasted 41 years."},{"time":806233,"text":"So whenever he said anything to me\nthat just seemed kind of non-psychopathic,"},{"time":809955,"text":"I thought to myself, well I'm not\ngoing to put that in my book."},{"time":813608,"text":"And then I realized that\nbecoming a psychopath spotter"},{"time":816936,"text":"had kind of turned me\na little bit psychopathic."},{"time":820436,"text":"Because I was desperate to shove him\nin a box marked \"Psychopath.\""},{"time":825404,"text":"I was desperate to define him\nby his maddest edges."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830138,"text":"And I realized, my God --"},{"time":831364,"text":"this is what I've been doing for 20 years."},{"time":833391,"text":"It's what all journalists do."},{"time":835037,"text":"We travel across the world\nwith our notepads in our hands,"},{"time":838521,"text":"and we wait for the gems."},{"time":840982,"text":"And the gems are always\nthe outermost aspects"},{"time":845339,"text":"of our interviewee's personality."},{"time":846992,"text":"And we stitch them together\nlike medieval monks,"},{"time":850490,"text":"and we leave the normal\nstuff on the floor."},{"time":854927,"text":"And you know, this is a country\nthat over-diagnoses"},{"time":857970,"text":"certain mental disorders hugely."},{"time":861271,"text":"Childhood bipolar --"},{"time":862637,"text":"children as young as four\nare being labeled bipolar"},{"time":866216,"text":"because they have temper tantrums,"},{"time":868670,"text":"which scores them high\non the bipolar checklist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":873273,"text":"When I got back to London, Tony phoned me."},{"time":877437,"text":"He said, \"Why haven't you\nbeen returning my calls?\""},{"time":880234,"text":"I said, \"Well, they say\nthat you're a psychopath.\""},{"time":883607,"text":"And he said, \"I'm not a psychopath.\""},{"time":885585,"text":"He said, \"You know what?"},{"time":886768,"text":"One of the items on the checklist\nis lack of remorse,"},{"time":889464,"text":"but another item on the checklist\nis cunning, manipulative."},{"time":892349,"text":"So when you say you feel\nremorse for your crime,"},{"time":894739,"text":"they say, 'Typical of the psychopath"},{"time":896503,"text":"to cunningly say he feels\nremorse when he doesn't.'"},{"time":899904,"text":"It's like witchcraft, they turn\neverything upside-down.\""},{"time":904321,"text":"He said, \"I've got a tribunal coming up."},{"time":906580,"text":"Will you come to it?\""},{"time":908740,"text":"So I said okay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910523,"text":"So I went to his tribunal."},{"time":912935,"text":"And after 14 years\nin Broadmoor, they let him go."},{"time":917841,"text":"They decided that he shouldn't\nbe held indefinitely"},{"time":920670,"text":"because he scores high\non a checklist that might mean"},{"time":924384,"text":"that he would have a greater\nthan average chance of recidivism."},{"time":929640,"text":"So they let him go."},{"time":931154,"text":"And outside in the corridor he said to me,"},{"time":933199,"text":"\"You know what, Jon?"},{"time":934841,"text":"Everyone's a bit psychopathic.\""},{"time":937620,"text":"He said, \"You are, I am.\nWell, obviously I am.\""},{"time":942016,"text":"I said, \"What are you going to do now?\""},{"time":944052,"text":"He said, \"I'm going to go to Belgium."},{"time":946259,"text":"There's a woman there that I fancy."},{"time":947961,"text":"But she's married, so I'm going to have\nto get her split up from her husband.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":951940,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":956075,"text":"Anyway, that was two years ago,"},{"time":959132,"text":"and that's where my book ended."},{"time":960734,"text":"And for the last 20 months,\neverything was fine."},{"time":966000,"text":"Nothing bad happened."},{"time":967385,"text":"He was living with a girl outside London."},{"time":969548,"text":"He was, according\nto Brian the Scientologist,"},{"time":971670,"text":"making up for lost time,\nwhich I know sounds ominous,"},{"time":974720,"text":"but isn't necessarily ominous."},{"time":976962,"text":"Unfortunately, after 20 months,"},{"time":978883,"text":"he did go back to jail for a month."},{"time":981617,"text":"He got into a \"fracas\"\nin a bar, he called it."},{"time":986104,"text":"Ended up going to jail for a month,\nwhich I know is bad,"},{"time":988769,"text":"but at least a month implies\nthat whatever the fracas was,"},{"time":992681,"text":"it wasn't too bad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":995069,"text":"And then he phoned me."},{"time":997802,"text":"And you know what, I think\nit's right that Tony is out."},{"time":1002898,"text":"Because you shouldn't define\npeople by their maddest edges."},{"time":1006077,"text":"And what Tony is,\nis he's a semi-psychopath."},{"time":1010332,"text":"He's a gray area in a world\nthat doesn't like gray areas."},{"time":1015796,"text":"But the gray areas\nare where you find the complexity."},{"time":1020792,"text":"It's where you find the humanity,"},{"time":1023237,"text":"and it's where you find the truth."},{"time":1026121,"text":"And Tony said to me,"},{"time":1028253,"text":"\"Jon, could I buy you a drink in a bar?"},{"time":1032149,"text":"I just want to thank you\nfor everything you've done for me.\""},{"time":1035473,"text":"And I didn't go."},{"time":1037674,"text":"What would you have done?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1040501,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1041877,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}